"***Question 1: \"How likely is it that Bond will escape from Le Chiffre?\"***\n1. Not very likely\n\nIt seems unlikely that Bond will escape from Le Chiffre and his two gunmen, given that they have already broken into his hotel room, outnumbered him, and searched him thoroughly, removing his revolver and leaving him feeling \"puny and impotent\".\n\n***Question 2: \"How suspenseful do you find this passage to be?\"***\n7. Extremely suspenseful\n\nThis passage is extremely suspenseful, as it sets up a tense and intense situation where the protagonist (Bond) is suddenly and unexpectedly attacked by his enemies. The reader is left wondering what will happen next, and the use of vivid and dynamic language (\"the door burst in toward him\", \"guns drawn\", \"he crashed to the ground\") creates a sense of urgency and danger.\n\nQuestion 1: 1. Not very likely\nQuestion 2: 7. Extremely suspenseful"